MSTest v4 removed `[ExpectedException]`. Replace it with **`Assert.ThrowsException<T>()`** (or `Assert.ThrowsExceptionAsync<T>()` for async methods) inside the test body:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}

[TestMethod]
public void Process_InvalidState_ThrowsInvalidOperation()
{
    Assert.ThrowsException<InvalidOperationException>(() => Process());
}
```

**Why the change:** `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` is more precise — it asserts only the specific call throws, not any line in the method. It also lets you inspect the returned exception (message, inner exception, etc.) if needed:

```csharp
var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
Assert.AreEqual("input", ex.ParamName);
```

